"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:2.19.2\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">2.19.2</span> Siege ramp, siege mound</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">סֹלְלָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(sollah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam20:15\">2SA 20:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:32\">2KI 19:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:33\">ISA 37:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:6\">JER 6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:24\">JER 32:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:4\">JER 33:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek4:2\">EZK 4:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:17\">EZK 17:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek21:27\">EZK 21:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:8\">EZK 26:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:15\">DAN 11:15</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description and usage:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0397_siege_ramp_en.jpg\" alt=\"Siege ramp at Masada, built by the Romans to attack the Jewish rebels who had taken refuge there\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">Siege ramp at Masada, built by the Romans to attack the Jewish rebels who had taken refuge there (© Andrew Shiva / Wikipedia, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>The siege ramp was a road leading up to the walls of a city that was under attack. Fortified cities were often built on high ground and were difficult to approach. Battering rams (see <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">2.19.7 Battering ram&lt;REALIA:2.19.7&gt;</a>) were very heavy and hard to move. The attackers would build a ramp or road over which they could bring their battering ram and other siege instruments.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>It is not always clear from the context if the Hebrew word <em>sollah</em> refers to a siege wall or to a ramp for an assault. Most translations choose something like “siege mound,” which will not be understood by most readers. In <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek4:2\">EZK 4:2</a><abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> has “earthworks,” which is more modern English but does not indicate the function of the structure. <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr> comes closer with “a ramp up to it.”</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
